Transcript.Content: Hello, I'm supposed to schedule an appointment.
Hey there! Sounds good. May I have your name?
It's Jane Doe.
Nice Ms. Doe. What service can I help you with today?
I need a dental check-up.
Of course. Do you prefer in-person or virtual appointments?
In person, if that's possible.
Let me check our available slots... We have times on April 14th at 10 AM and 1 PM.
Hmm, I'm working during noon. Maybe the 10 AM would be better.
Okay, booking that for you. What's your name?
My name is John Smith. Oh, wait, that's my brother's appointment.
Right, Mr. Smith here. I got it right. Let's get some details...
Address is 123 Maple Street. Do they need the full address?
Just to confirm our records, may I have your email too?
Sure, john.smith@email.com.
Perfect account info. So we've scheduled you for April 14th at 10 AM with Dr. Emily White.
Sounds good. Thank you so much. Do I need a reminder?
We'll send you an email confirmation and a reminder the day before.
Alright, see you then!
Great! Take care, Ms. Smith.
